sentences: Labinot Gashi (pronounced [gaˈʃi]; born 4 October 1989), known mononymously as Gashi (stylised as GASHI), is an American rapper, singer and songwriter.
Labinot Gashi was born in Libya, on October 4, 1989, to ethnic Albanian parents from Kosovo.
Although Gashi earned honors during his first year in college, he decided to drop out of college and concentrate more on music.
Gashi won several music contests and he was the winner of "First Time Performances" of First Look Sessions in both 2010 and 2011.
His debut project, the mixtape Last of a Rare Breed (2011) was hosted by Erkman, and featured tracks with Nipsey Hussle and French Montana.
